&lt;h3&gt;Senior Solutions Architect, Enterprise Products&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Jane Street Group, LLC has multiple openings for a Senior Solutions Architect, Enterprise Products in New York, NY.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The position duties are as follows:&amp;nbsp; Lead the research, selection, installation, integration, and management of our third-party applications, ensuring enterprise products are strategically configured and customized to meet the company&#39;s evolving needs. Day-to-day duties include:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own the entire application lifecycle, from procurement and cybersecurity review through implementation, production release, and ongoing support;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive the research and selection of enterprise solutions, conducting vendor assessments and making architectural recommendations that align with business objectives;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead cross-functional collaboration with Procurement, Cybersecurity, Legal, and IT Operations teams to ensure successful onboarding and integration of third-party applications;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design and implement enterprise features and integrations, including SSO, access controls, and system customizations, while managing technical debt and maintenance priorities;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with trading desks and international offices to understand business requirements and deliver solutions that enhance efficiency and effectiveness across the firm;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide technical leadership and mentorship to junior team members, establishing best practices for application management and troubleshooting;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Produce comprehensive technical documentation and analysis to inform stakeholders of system capabilities, risks, and improvement opportunities;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive continuous improvement initiatives by identifying optimization opportunities, proposing architectural enhancements, and leading the implementation of custom configurations that better serve business needs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The position requires a 3 or 4 year Bachelor’s degree in Information Technology, Computer Science, Software Engineering, Engineering, or a related technological field or foreign equivalent plus&amp;nbsp; 4 years of progressively responsible experience in any occupation where experience managing third-party applications in a financial or technology firm is gained. Experience must include:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;4 years of experience using a common enterprise platform (e.g., Salesforce, ServiceNow, Workday, collaboration tools, identity management systems), including 2 years of experience with Jira, Confluence, Slack, and Google Workspace;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;4 years of experience managing SSO implementations, API integrations, data synchronization, and middleware technologies including SAML, SCIM, JIT, and REST APIs;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;3 years of hands-on experience in the complete software delivery lifecycle, including stakeholder requirements analysis, solution assessment, integration work, and production rollout;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;2 years of experience contributing to threat models for vendor integrations, including information gathering, participation in security-risk assessments, and analysis of system architecture and data flows;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;2 years of experience integrating third-party applications with internally developed&amp;nbsp; infrastructure written in Python and OCaml, including implementing API integrations with external services, configuring SSO authentication, and developing integration layers primarily in Python with some OCaml to connect third-party application APIs to internally developed technology systems;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;2 years of experience supporting distributed technical and non-technical teams across time zones and regulatory jurisdictions;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;All technical requirements for this role may be subject to employer conducted testing to assess minimum proficiency.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Part-time telecommuting may be permitted with manager approval.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ref. SSAEP26&lt;/p&gt;
